%N A393848 O.g.f. A(x) satisfies: [x^n] exp( n^8 * x ) / A(x) = 0 for n>0.
%H A393848 Paul D. Hanna, <a href="/A393848/b393848.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..100</a>
%e A393848 O.g.f.: A(x) = 1 + x + 32513*x^2 + 46836819846*x^3 + 765428206086770699*x^4 + 75487364859452767380638650*x^5 + 31055662784066179594203178121671298*x^6 + ...
%e A393848 ILLUSTRATION OF DEFINITION.
%e A393848 The table of coefficients of x^k/k! in exp(n^8*x)/A(x) begins
%e A393848   n = 1: [1,      0,       -65025,     -281020724000, ...];
%e A393848   n = 2: [1,    255,            0,     -281053886750, ...];
%e A393848   n = 3: [1,   6560,     42968575,                 0, ...];
%e A393848   n = 4: [1,  65535,   4294771200,   281168287041250, 0, ...];
%e A393848   n = 5: [1, 390624, 152587044351, 59603829791189824, 23263957046308867252101, 0, ...];
%e A393848   ...
%e A393848 in which a diagonal, the coefficient of x^n in row n, is all zeros.
%o A393848 (PARI) {a(n,k=8) = my(A=[1]); for(i=1, n, A=concat(A, 0); m=#A; A[m] = Vec( exp(x*(m-1)^k +x*O(x^m)) / Ser(A) )[m] ); A[n+1]}
%o A393848 for(n=0, 15, print1( a(n,8), ", "))
%Y A393848 Sequences below with the given parameter p have an o.g.f. F(x) satisfying [x^n] exp( n^p*x ) / F(x) = 0 for n >= 1.
